The paper deals with graph embeddings and their distortion, which are topics commonly studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS, cs.GT). The use of probabilistic methods and analysis of randomized algorithms suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of randomized algorithms (cs.DM) and stochastic processes (cs.SI).
